    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fbf6f19a_39798430",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T23:57:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This was supposed to Chuck buffered but unconsumed input from stdin, because it would belong to the parent, not the child. This follows a fork() which Fuchsia doesn\u0027t have, so the whole implementation is bogus on Fuchsia. I\u0027m sure we could concoct a MultiprocessExec implementation using whatever Fuchsia\u0027s spawn-process operation is, but it wouldn\u0027t be anything like the POSIX branch here.",
      "parentUuid": "300e4813_f445061f",
      "revId": "21111ee7d1f46f7bda8e5d9ba080db35796449cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4dad19a_4ab5a6a0",
        "filename": "test/multiprocess_exec_posix.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 93,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T00:06:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, there\u0027s no fork() for sure. OK, makes more sense to exclude this whole file instead. I also dropped util/double_fork_and_exec.cc for the same reason.",
      "parentUuid": "fbf6f19a_39798430",
      "revId": "21111ee7d1f46f7bda8e5d9ba080db35796449cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7d1ff513_e9333e67",
        "filename": "util/posix/close_multiple.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T23:46:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "While I believe this is technically correct, it points to one of the trickier parts of this port and that\u0027s the dichotomy between POSIX and Fuchsia-proper. This should now close all fds, as it does on other \nPOSIXs, but that\u0027s not the same as closing all the zx_handle_ts that refer to files.\n\nChromium chose to make Fuchsia an is_posix\u003dtrue (and I think is probably correct to do so) to ease porting and maintenance. But files are one place where there\u0027s definitely multiple options, and not everything is an fd.",
      "revId": "21111ee7d1f46f7bda8e5d9ba080db35796449cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "79efb730_ca77502e",
        "filename": "util/posix/close_multiple.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T23:57:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also depends: what\u0027s Fuchsia\u0027s inheritance policy for both file descriptors and zx_handle_ts in spawned processes?",
      "parentUuid": "7d1ff513_e9333e67",
      "revId": "21111ee7d1f46f7bda8e5d9ba080db35796449cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d1c51e3_42eb9abb",
        "filename": "util/posix/close_multiple.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T00:06:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Very explicit, each one must be specifically cloned or passed into the child, with a bit of specialness for stdin/stdout/stderr. I think again, that means I should just exclude this file on Fuchsia.",
      "parentUuid": "79efb730_ca77502e",
      "revId": "21111ee7d1f46f7bda8e5d9ba080db35796449cc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
